With the adopted parameters (\teff=5159, \logg=2.1, [Fe/H]=--1.8), we derived these possible masses and ages (see Fig.\,\ref{fig:iso}):
\begin{itemize}
\item $\rm M=2.3 M_\odot$ and age of 493\,Ma (3, RGB, red giant branch, or the quick stage of red giant for intermediate+massive stars\footnote{\url{http://stev.oapd.inaf.it/cmd_3.1/faq.html}}); 
\item $\rm M=2.3 M_\odot$ and age of 504\,Ma (4, CHEB, core He-burning for low mass stars, or the very initial stage of CHeB for intermediate+massive stars);
\item $\rm M=1.9 M_\odot$ and age of 904\,Ma (7, EAGB, the early asymptotic giant branch).

